Travels through Virginia. [ From Theodor de Bry's 'America', Vol. I, 1590, after a drawing of John White]. - caption: ''Their sitting at meate'. Engraving of two figures seated on a strip of matting, eating with their right hands from a large circular dish containing grains of food. The woman wears a necklace of beads, and a fringed skin robe over her left shoulder. The man wears a fringed deerskin mantle. On the mat is a gourd water vessel with carved out handle, skin bag, tobacco pipe, walnut, fish, four ears of maize, and a scallop shell.'
